41:27.487 --> 41:29.350
They didn't want a major war with the United 
States. And as long as we didn't invade the North

41:31.490 --> 41:39.681
and try to occupy the North, but only prevent the 
North from taking over the South, it would have

41:31.490 --> 41:39.681
been status quo. Johnson's lack of political will 
and leadership, I'm convinced, doomed 55,000

41:40.803 --> 41:56.864
Americans to die and close to half a million to be 
wounded because the war dragged out so long.

41:56.884 --> 41:58.206
People say that it was... It was Johnson's 
personal war. What do you think of that? Well, it

42:00.745 --> 42:02.867
was being directed for the most part. I think he had 
delusions of being a Churchill the way he had his,

42:02.927 --> 42:10.817
from what I can understand, his bunker set up under 
the White House there with his little war

42:02.927 --> 42:10.817
situation room. I don't know this.

